<!--
Day 43 Project: Using Color in CSS
Course: 100 Days of Code: The Complete Python Pro Bootcamp by Dr. Angela Yu
Description:
This HTML page shows a clean design with a chosen color scheme applied via CSS.
It demonstrates background color, heading color, paragraph text color,
and accessible contrast for readability.
-->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Color Styling Example</title>
  <style>
    /* Light gray background for easy reading */
    body {
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 30px;
      color: #333333; /* Dark text for contrast */
    }

    /* Vibrant orange heading color to catch attention */
    h1 {
      color: #ff5733;
    }

    /* Slightly softer dark gray for paragraph text */
    p {
      color: #4d4d4d;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 600px;
    }

    /* Link color with hover effect */
    a {
      color: #0077cc;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
      color: #005999;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to My Colorful Webpage</h1>
  <p>
    This is an example paragraph demonstrating good color choices.
    The background is a soft light gray, and the text is dark enough
    for excellent readability and accessibility.
  </p>
  <p>
    Visit 
    <a href="https://coolors.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Coolors.co
    </a> 
    to explore amazing color palettes.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
